    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1932-11-29T16:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1932-11-29T16:00:00-05:00" n="614"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d614">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">837.00/3399: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Cuba</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Guggenheim</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Habana</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1932-11-29T16:00:00-05:00"
                            >November 29, 1932—4 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received 5:25 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>121. <persName corresp="#p_MGP1">Mendieta</persName> and <persName
                        corresp="#p_MPCR1">Méndez Peñate</persName> were released from prison today
                    and orders are being issued to set free more than 80 other political prisoners
                    not held on definite charges of serious criminal offenses. Thirty-three military
                    supervisors have been withdrawn from various points.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Guggenheim</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
